The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                A drunk woman in her late 30s drowned in Rabindra Sarobar on Sunday morning after suffering a cardiac arrest while taking a dip.   ccording to police, Manasi Debnath, who lived in a Lake Gardens shanty, fought with her husband Sukhlal on Saturday night and had been drinking since then. She headed to Rabindra Sarobar around 10am. Neighbours did not stop her thinking a dip will do her good.  bout two hours later, her body was found floating several metres from the spot where she was seen taking a dip. Police took Manasi to MR Bangur Hospital, where doctors declared her dead. A preliminary examination revealed, she had suffered a cardiac arrest.     A middle-aged man who is yet to be identified was crushed under the wheels of a private bus at the Prince Anwar Shah Road-DP Sashmal Road crossing on Sunday evening. The man was taken to MR Bangur Hospital where he was declared brought dead. Police said he was trying to cross the road when the bus hit him. The body has been sent for post-mortem.    Two children received minor injuries when an SUV mounted a footpath on Humayun Kabir Sarani, under New Alipore police station, on Sunday afternoon. According to police, the woman driving the vehicle lost control while trying to steer past a boy crossing the road. On seeing the vehicle heading towards the footpath, most pedestrians ran away but the children couldnt. The windscreen of the car was smashed as it mounted the pavement. Police impounded the vehicle.     Three youths were arrested in the Girish Park area on Sunday for allegedly assaulting trader Mrinal Dey after he refused to pay subscription for a local clubs cultural programme. Police said Krishnendu Burman, Pratik Burman and Santosh Singh had demanded a hefty sum.    Mohammad Shauqat, 35, was found lying unconscious on Kachhi Sadak in Garden Reach on Sunday afternoon. There was a deep wound in his abdomen. A police patrol team rushed him to SSKM where he was declared brought dead. Police have started a murder case. Residents said Shauqat was a drug addict.     Arindam Sarkar, 30, was arrested in Agarpara on Sunday evening on the charge of operating a motorcycle theft racket. Police said Arindam was wanted in theft cases in Titagarh, Sodepur and Belghoria. He had stolen at least 14 motorcycles in the past two months, said an officer.    Harishan Halui, 27, a labourer in an onion godown, collapsed on MG Road on Sunday afternoon. He was rushed to Medical College and Hospital, where he was declared brought dead. Police said he died of heart attack.    Amina Bibi, 19, died after consuming poison in her Bishnupur home early on Sunday. Her parents alleged that she was being tortured by her husband and in-laws for dowry for the past couple of months. Her husband Aslam, a trader, is absconding. They married six months ago.             
